
	<sn><md>## Rural vs Urban{.text-center}

![diagram-rural-vs-urban](https://theraise.eu/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Artboard5-1024x565-1.png)

| Characteristics          | Rural Settlements                                                   | Urban Settlements                                                             |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Population Size**      | Small population, low density                                       | Large population, high density                                                |
| **Main Occupation**      | Agriculture, fishing, forestry, mining (primary activities)         | Industry, trade, transport, services (secondary &amp; tertiary activities)        |
| **Settlement Pattern**   | Dispersed, clustered, or linear, often irregular                    | Planned, compact, nucleated with grid or radial patterns                      |
| **Infrastructure**       | Limited roads, electricity, water supply, and healthcare facilities | Advanced infrastructure with transport, hospitals, schools, and entertainment |
| **Social Life**          | Close-knit, traditional, community-based                            | Diverse, modern, individualistic, cosmopolitan                                |
| **Economic Development** | Subsistence economy, limited employment opportunities               | Commercial economy, varied job opportunities, higher income levels            |
| **Environment**          | Natural surroundings, open space, greenery                          | Artificial environment, high pollution, less open space                       |
| **Cultural Features**    | Traditional lifestyle, folk culture, strong customs                 | Modern lifestyle, exposure to global culture, fast-paced life                 |
| **Governance**           | Local self-government (panchayat, village councils)                 | Municipal corporations, metropolitan authorities                              |
| **Growth Trend**         | Slow change, gradual growth                                         | Rapid expansion, urban sprawl, and migration-driven growth                    |
</md></sn>		
